ns = lambda : readline().rstrip()
ni = lambda : int(readline().rstrip())
nm = lambda : map(int, readline().split())
nl = lambda : list(map(int, readline().split()))

def solve():
    (u, v) = nm()
    if u == v:
        if u == 0:
            print(0)
        else:
            print(1)
            print(u)
        return
    elif u > v:
        print(-1)
        return
    w = v - u
    if w & 1:
        print(-1)
    else:
        l = [u, w // 2, w // 2]
        if not l[0] & l[-1]:
            l[0] ^= l.pop()
        print(len(l))
        print(*l)
    return
